OL,3,CSon calls for assisted dying reform
OL,4,Cafter father dies alone in garden
OL,6,FA son whose father took his own life
OL,7,Fafter suffering with prostate cancer
OL,8,Fis calling for a change in the law on
OL,9,Fassisted dying.
OL,11,FThree years ago, Gareth Ward's father
OL,12,FNorman, called him to tell him he
OL,13,Fcould not endure another night of pain
OL,14,Fas his condition was deteriorating. He
OL,15,Fdied on his own, in his garden in
OL,16,FGravesend, Kent.
OL,18,FGareth Ward said: "He wanted the pain
OL,19,Fto stop and he felt there was no other
OL,20,Foption.
