OL,3,CSon calls for assisted dying reform
OL,4,Cafter father dies alone in garden
OL,6,FRt Rev Richard Moth, Bishop of Arundel
OL,7,Fand Brighton said: "If you look at any
OL,8,Fother country in the world, that has
OL,9,Fintroduced this kind of legislation,
OL,10,Fit's always been the beginning of what
OL,11,FI might describe as a slippery slope.
OL,13,F"The pressures on people to take this
OL,14,Froute becomes easier and easier, and
OL,15,Fthen the pressure on people to take
OL,16,Fthis route becomes greater."
OL,18,FAssisting someone to end their life is
OL,19,Fcurrently illegal in England, Wales
OL,20,Fand Northern Ireland, with a maximum
OL,21,Fprison sentence of 14 years.
